[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837759026783&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837759026783&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

If you're running 4.3BSD, the sendmail that came with your system doesn't
support MX.  However, Berkeley has a new sendmail that does support MX.
If you have 4.3 and are on the ARPA Internet, I encourage you to install
this version of sendmail.  If you have 4.2, I suspect it will work if you
are otherwise using BIND, but I don't know for sure.  If you are using
MMDF rather than sendmail, I believe CSNET has a version of MMDF available
that will support MX.

RFC 973 provides updates to RFC 882 and 883 and includes
the specifications on how MXs are stored in the nameserver databases.

RFC 974 explains how the SMTP mail systems actually interpret the MXs.

An MX supporting sendmail can be found on ucbarpa.Berkeley.EDU by
logging in as anonymous and retrieving pub/4.3/sendmail.MX.tar
The file is 1.26MB.

	Mark

